	(2111,'_transient__sol_cache_872','a:3:{s:6:\"slider\";a:7:{i:877;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-11.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 1\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 1\";s:7:\"caption\";s:411:\"Chances are youve heard that identity theft is a growing concern in America. But what about medical identity theft?  Your personal information is stored in many different databases and handled by lots of different people, which could make you a target for medical identity theft. [1]\n\nHere are some places where your medical identity is stored and what to look for when dealing with your medical information.\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:878;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-21.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 2\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 2\";s:7:\"caption\";s:316:\"<strong>The Doctors Office: </strong> Doctors appointments are a necessity of life, but your medical records and personal information arent always 100% secure. Make sure to read your Explanation of Benefits (EOB) statement to be sure youre not being charged for medical services you didnt receive. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:873;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:111:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-3.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:59:\"Pharmacy: Concerned Pharmacist Calling About a Prescription\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:59:\"Pharmacy: Concerned Pharmacist Calling About a Prescription\";s:7:\"caption\";s:298:\"<strong>The Pharmacy:</strong> Last time you checked, you didnt order a prescription for Ritalin but somehow its showing up on your EOB statement. Identity thieves could use your personal information to fill prescriptions, so its really important to review all prescription statements. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:874;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:111:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-4.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:38:\"Blood Bank: Nurse Talks to Blood Donor\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:38:\"Blood Bank: Nurse Talks to Blood Donor\";s:7:\"caption\";s:242:\"<strong>The Lab:</strong> Getting blood drawn isnt always fun, but neither is getting your identity stolen. Pay close attention to your credit report to ensure you dont receive a medical collection notice that you dont recognize. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:875;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-51.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 5\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 5\";s:7:\"caption\";s:260:\"<strong>Your Workplace: </strong>Enrolling in benefits means that youre probably sharing a lot of personal data. If youre denied insurance based on an existing condition that you never had, this could be a sign that you are a victim of medical fraud. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:876;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:112:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/27-Image-Carousel-Medical-Fraud-Slide-61.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 6\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:51:\"27  Image Carousel  Medical Fraud  Slide 6\";s:7:\"caption\";s:323:\"<strong>Your Wallet:</strong> Between credit cards, loyalty rewards, and your drivers license, your Social Security card may seem like just another item to stash