pe\";s:5:\"image\";}i:901;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:110:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/30-Image-Carousel-Child-Safety-Slide-4.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:50:\"30  Image Carousel  Child Safety  Slide 4\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:50:\"30  Image Carousel  Child Safety  Slide 4\";s:7:\"caption\";s:235:\"<strong>Withdraws from friends: </strong>One week theyre best friends and want a sleepover every night, and the next week no one is coming over to your house. Your child may refuse to spend time with friends or age related peers.[1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:902;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:110:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/30-Image-Carousel-Child-Safety-Slide-5.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:50:\"30  Image Carousel  Child Safety  Slide 5\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:50:\"30  Image Carousel  Child Safety  Slide 5\";s:7:\"caption\";s:205:\"<strong>Stresses about attending school: </strong>Your child may not want to go to school and may start to mention that they hate their classes, their teachers, or some other aspect of their academics. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:903;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:110:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/30-Image-Carousel-Child-Safety-Slide-6.jpg\";s:5:\"title\";s:50:\"30  Image Carousel  Child Safety  Slide 6\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";s:3:\"alt\";s:50:\"30  Image Carousel  Child Safety  Slide 6\";s:7:\"caption\";s:234:\"<strong>Displays depression-like symptoms:</strong> Cyberbullying can take a huge emotional toll on a young individual. You might notice that your child eats less, has a hard time sleeping, or becomes irritated over little things. [1]\";s:4:\"type\";s:5:\"image\";}i:1010;a:7:{s:6:\"status\";s:6:\"active\";s:3:\"src\";s:109:\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/MetLife-Defender-Logo-Image-Galleries.jpg\