	(946,8,'2014-08-13 16:19:51','2014-08-13 16:19:51','<p>The statistics are staggering: Hacking and internal corporate fraud are steadily rising. So how do you keep your family safe?</p>\r\n<p>No doubt about it: 2013 was the worst year for identity fraud in U.S. history. More than 500 million personal records were exposed to hackers or thieves leaving 13 million people victims of identity fraud.<sup>1,2</sup></p>\r\n<p>Breaches ranged from credit card number exposures to medical record thefts and, if the first half of 2014 is any indication, these cases will continue to rise. In fact, according to the Identity Theft Resource Center, 368 breaches have occurred this year so far - that\'s up nearly 19 percent from the same period last year!<sup>1</sup></p>\r\n<p><strong>Can this trend be stopped? </strong></p>\r\n<p>While online breaches are becoming more fact than fiction, by taking control of your digital life you can write your own ending to the story.</p>\r\n<p>Practicing the basics can go a long way. Keep your passwords complex and updated, check your online accounts for suspicious behaviors, and stay up-to-date on the latest Internet protection tips at MetLifeDefender.com.</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-802\" src=\"https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/19-Infographic-The-Year-of-the-Data-Breach_v4-page-001.jpg\" alt=\"19 - Infographic - The Year of the Data Breach_v4-page-001\" width=\"1744\" height=\"1718\" /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0714384027[exp0715][All States][DC]</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">L0714383422[exp0715][All States][DC]</span></p>','The Year of the Data Breach','','publish','open','open','','the-year-of-the-data-breach','','','2014-08-13 16:22:33','2014-08-13 16:22:33','',0,'https://toolsandtips.metlifedefender.com/?p=946',0,'post','',0),
